main event: A witness in Kemah, Texas observed a spider-like material floating in the sky for a long while in Spring 1961.
interesting points: The material was floating 1-2 feet above the ground, drifting slowly over the horizon.
There was no sound, odor, smoke, or trail associated with the object.
Station personnel observed the object for several hours as it moved steadily over the horizon.
The object did not pulsate, flash, or rotate.
The witness could not determine the origin of the material and it was deemed unidentified.
sighted object: spider-like material floating in the sky
